HEADWORD: Ceratohyal
<hw>Cer`a*to*hy"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ke`ras</grk> horn + the letter ⟦UPSILON⟧.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to the bone, or cartilage, below the epihyal in the
hyoid arch.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A ceratohyal bone, or
cartilage, which, in man, forms one of the small horns of the
hyoid.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ceratophyllaceae</ent>⟦br⟧
